<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>About a month ago i asked here for help choosing music for my dad&#39;s funeral and got so many helpful and lovely responses. </p> <p>I wanted to thank you all and in case anyone wanted to know I went with </p> <p>Max richter -on the nature of daylight </p> <p>brahms- A major intermezzo opp.118, no.2</p> <p>Bach- sleepers awake! (As soon as I heard this piece I remembered my dad playing it to me and saying it was a wonderful piece of music. So I played it at the entrance to the crematorium so it was the last music he ever &#39;heard&#39;</p> <p>London philharmonic orchestra -enigma variations: nimrod </p> <p>The whole thing went really well and I have now discovered a lot of beautiful songs so thank you all again.</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/half_deer"> /u/half_deer </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/classicalmusic/comments/wddqpy/a_thank_you_for_helping_me_choose_music_for_my/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/classicalmusic/comments/wddqpy/a_thank_you_for_helping_me_choose_music_for_my/">[comments]</a></span>